The paper deals with detecting new information and events in a dynamic network, which involves analyzing influence properties in a network and detecting failure propagation. This suggests that the paper could belong to the sub-categories of Social and Information Networks (cs.SI), Systems and Control (cs.SY), and Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS). The paper also involves using a probing schedule to choose a small set of nodes to check for new items, which could fall under the sub-category of Information Theory (cs.IT). Finally, the paper presents an algorithm for computing the optimal schedule through convex optimization, which could be related to the sub-category of Machine Learning (cs.LG).
